Question:
Count how many elements are greater than 50.
Input:
List<Integer> list = Arrays.asList(10, 55, 60, 35, 85);

Solutions:
Java 8 Streams count elements >50 using filter with predicate then count(). For input [10, 55, 60, 35, 85], returns and prints 3.

#Step-by-Step Logic
Stream the list via stream(). Filter with filter(num -> num > 50). Call count() terminal for matching count as long.

#Complete Implementation

import java.util.Arrays;
import java.util.List;

public class CountGreaterThan50 {
    public static void countAndPrintGreaterThan50(List<Integer> numbers) {
        long count = numbers.stream()
                            .filter(num -> num > 50)
                            .count();
        System.out.println(count);
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        List<Integer> list = Arrays.asList(10, 55, 60, 35, 85);
        countAndPrintGreaterThan50(list);
    }
}

Prints 3. 

Processes full stream; O(n) time.

#Thought Process
filter intermediate selects >50 (predicate boolean). count() terminal reduces to size. Simple, declarative vs manual loop. Returns long for large lists.

#Edge Cases Analysis
Empty list: Returns 0L.
Null list: NPE on stream(); null-check.
Null elements: null > 50 false (no NPE).
All â‰¤50: 0.
All >50: Returns size.
Exactly 50: Filtered out (> strict).
Negatives: false. Large: Fine up to Integer.MAX_VALUE.
